x &= \sqrt{7} & x &= 2 & x &= \pm \sqrt{3}
\end{align*} So $x$ cannot be $\sqrt{7},$ 2 or $\pm \sqrt{3}.$<answer>$$\sqrt{7} - 2 + \sqrt{3}$$</answer>

